    <DocumentationNarrative Id="source:cli:meta-datavault-raw:app:narrative:guide:working-with-raw-data-vault" DocumentationSubjectId="source:cli:meta-datavault-raw:app" PreviousNarrativeId="source:cli:meta-datavault-raw:app:narrative:summary:summary">
      <Body>MetaRawDataVault models the source-faithful Data Vault layer. Hubs, links, satellites, source keys, and their relationships are declared as durable structures that capture identity, association, and historized source evidence.

The raw vault begins from a modeled source contract rather than a folder of database scripts. Its workspace provides the design surface between an extracted schema and a physical implementation, so the important choices remain visible before SQL is generated: which source identities form hubs, which associations form links, and which descriptive attributes belong in satellites.

The model keeps raw evidence distinct from business interpretation. That separation supports auditable ingestion, controlled regeneration, and a clear handoff to the Business Data Vault and warehouse layers without losing the connection to the systems that supplied the data.</Body>
